                <h1>George Marshall: Architect of WWII Success</h1>
                <p>George Marshall was a pivotal figure in World War II, serving as the U.S. Army Chief of Staff and later as Secretary of State. He orchestrated the massive mobilization of American troops and supplies, leading to Allied victories. His legacy is cemented by the Marshall Plan, which aimed at rebuilding Europe after the war.</p>
